         <abstract id="aspace_7bf7dae3bad30f5deb64dd35a863e9d9">A collection of United States postage stamps compiled by Meade and Mildred B. Minnigerode on the topic of pioneer life in the United States.</abstract>
    
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_d730adb15d4bc70a018819836654ee19">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Donated by Mrs. Mildred B. Minnigerode through Archibald Hanna, Jr.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_0e3456cc76eb3271c1b45ef7c50a7955">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research. Due to the physical nature of the material, staff supervision is required.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_559f1aa25309d1e5961f151d97eb8051">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>United States Pioneer History on United States Stamps Collection. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_8d9da8e342e3d52c50ad5b05fb8fca5e">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The U.S. Pioneer History on U.S. Stamps Collection contains nine volumes plus three supplementary volumes compiled by Meade and Mildred Minnigerode; organized topically and chronologically and including mainly American stamps of commemorative issue in blocks of four, covers and photographs of stamps together with illustrative material, maps and holograph descriptive commentary.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <userestrict id="aspace_229f188d58d67838bb45a690fcbb8bfe">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>Copyright status for collection materials is unknown. Transmission or reproduction of materials protected by U.S. Copyright Law (Title 17, U.S.C.) beyond that allowed by fair use requires the written permission of the copyright owners. Works not in the public domain cannot be commercially exploited without permission of the copyright owners. Responsibility for any use rests exclusively with the user.</p>  
      </userestrict>
